@startuml
title Cart data flow with classic Redux structure

actor User
participant "ProductDetail / UI Component" as UI
participant "cartAction.ts\n(action creators)" as Action
participant "cartStore.ts\n(Redux Store)" as Store
participant "cartReducer.ts\n(reducer)" as Reducer
participant "Header / Cart Page / Checkout UI" as ConsumerUI

== Add product to cart ==
User -> UI : Click "Add to cart"
UI -> Action : addToCart(payload)
Action --> UI : { type: ADD_TO_CART, payload }

UI -> Store : dispatch(action)
Store -> Reducer : cartReducer(prevState, action)

alt same productId + same size + same color exists
    Reducer -> Reducer : increase existing line quantity
else new cart line
    Reducer -> Reducer : push new item into cart
end

Reducer --> Store : nextState
Store --> UI : notify state updated
Store --> ConsumerUI : notify subscribed components

UI -> Store : getState() / selector
ConsumerUI -> Store : getState() / selector

Store --> UI : updated cart state
Store --> ConsumerUI : updated cart state

UI --> User : Add-to-cart feedback updated
ConsumerUI --> User : Header count / cart list / summary updated


== Increase quantity ==
User -> ConsumerUI : Click "+"
ConsumerUI -> Action : increaseCartItemQuantity(payload)
Action --> ConsumerUI : { type: INCREASE_CART_ITEM_QUANTITY, payload }
ConsumerUI -> Store : dispatch(action)
Store -> Reducer : cartReducer(prevState, action)
Reducer -> Reducer : find correct cart line
Reducer -> Reducer : quantity += 1
Reducer --> Store : nextState
Store --> ConsumerUI : notify update
ConsumerUI -> Store : getState() / selector
Store --> ConsumerUI : updated cart state
ConsumerUI --> User : Quantity and totals updated


== Decrease quantity ==
User -> ConsumerUI : Click "-"
ConsumerUI -> Action : decreaseCartItemQuantity(payload)
Action --> ConsumerUI : { type: DECREASE_CART_ITEM_QUANTITY, payload }
ConsumerUI -> Store : dispatch(action)
Store -> Reducer : cartReducer(prevState, action)

alt quantity > 1
    Reducer -> Reducer : quantity -= 1
else quantity == 1 and business rule is remove
    Reducer -> Reducer : remove item from cart
end

Reducer --> Store : nextState
Store --> ConsumerUI : notify update
ConsumerUI -> Store : getState() / selector
Store --> ConsumerUI : updated cart state
ConsumerUI --> User : Quantity/cart UI updated


== Remove item ==
User -> ConsumerUI : Click "Remove"
ConsumerUI -> Action : removeCartItem(payload)
Action --> ConsumerUI : { type: REMOVE_CART_ITEM, payload }
ConsumerUI -> Store : dispatch(action)
Store -> Reducer : cartReducer(prevState, action)
Reducer -> Reducer : remove correct cart line identity
Reducer --> Store : nextState
Store --> ConsumerUI : notify update
ConsumerUI -> Store : getState() / selector
Store --> ConsumerUI : updated cart state
ConsumerUI --> User : Item removed from cart UI


== Clear cart ==
User -> ConsumerUI : Click "Clear cart"
ConsumerUI -> Action : clearCart()
Action --> ConsumerUI : { type: CLEAR_CART }
ConsumerUI -> Store : dispatch(action)
Store -> Reducer : cartReducer(prevState, action)
Reducer -> Reducer : state.items = []
Reducer --> Store : nextState
Store --> ConsumerUI : notify update
ConsumerUI -> Store : getState() / selector
Store --> ConsumerUI : updated empty cart state
ConsumerUI --> User : Empty cart UI rendered

@enduml